CSS Comments
-not displayed in browser
-helps document source code


CSS Comments
-explain the code
-may help you edit source code at later date
-comments ignored by browsers
-placed inside <style> element and starts with /* and ends with */:
ex.
/* This is a single-line comment */
p {
  color: red;
}

can add comments wherever you want in code:
ex.
p {
  color: red; /* Set text color to red */
}

Comments can also span multiple lines:
ex.
/* This is
a mult-line
comment */

p {
  color: red;
}




HTML and CSS Comments
-can add comments to your HTML source by using <!-- ... -->
ex.
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>A Title</title>
    <style>
      p {
        color: red; /* Set text color to red */
      }
    </style>
  </head>


  <body>
    <h2> My Heading </h2>


    <!-- These paragraphs will be red.  -->
    <p> </p>
    <p> </p>
    <p> </p>

  </body>

</html>

